snippet.textDisplay: Shortly after I uploaded #1000, I decided this would be the theme I'd go with for #2000 and keep the video pure (well, almost!) and simple. This is THE video game theme and there's no need for words, really. As I said in the previous upload, I also feel like that #1000 video was special and I want to keep it that way. I do however want to use this Comments section to thank all of you for the continued support after all these years and give you each a digital thumbs up for helping me create and evolve such a nice VGM community, we did this together. To you who has been following me since the beginning, for a couple years or even just a couple days. It will soon be 10 years since I started this project, which is honestly mindblowing when you think how old we were then. I still remember how obscure the VGM scene was back then and how I thought nobody would really care about my videos, thinking I was one of those "weird nerdy people who like music from video games". I'm sure glad I was wrong and decided to upload that Wild Arms Town theme. I'm also very glad my lazy self decided to go with an unranked list because frankly, that's what kept me going for all these years: uploading whatever track I feel like, whenever I can, without any pressure, with an awesome community.

snippet.textDisplay:
Supradarky. Video game music is what got me into making music. Tifa's theme of FFVII is what got me playing the piano. Now I play guitar, piano and sing in my own band and perform self written songs. So to me VGM was always something special. 

I was so happy to find your playlist in 2011. I was delighted not only by the music but also by your comments about the games, especially every 100th game introduction. Every month I was looking forward to listening to a whole set of new songs. And i've listened through all of them. Wrote my favourites on a piece of paper and added them to my own collection. Of which maybe a hundred have a permanent spot on my phone!

 So thank you for all the effort over the years!

snippet.textDisplay: Congratulations on hitting 2000, Gabe.  I have been following this channel since #1025 and since then i have learned so much about great VGM and how it can really help a game become very memorable.  You were also my main inspiration to start writing blogs on VGM; i had to stop doing them because i was getting burned out and it became a big production putting them together.  Thank you for being so awesome to chat with and teaching us so much about great games and music.
